        "procedure": {
            "id": "procedure",
            "title": "Procedure",
            "isApplicable": true,
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "list",
                    "style": "ordered",
                    "items": [
                        "Open Xilinx ISE and create a new project targeting the appropriate FPGA device.",
                        "Create a new Verilog source file and write the full adder module using the assign statement for Sum (XOR of all inputs) and Carry (majority function).",
                        "Create the User Constraints File (UCF) mapping the three input ports (a, b, c) and two output ports (Sum, Carry) to the designated FPGA pin locations.",
                        "**Hardware Layout:** Typically, map `a`, `b`, `c` to the rightmost toggle switches and `Sum`, `Carry` to the adjacent LEDs.",
                        "Run the behavioural simulation in ISim by applying all 8 input combinations and verifying the outputs match the truth table.",
                        "Synthesize and implement the design in Xilinx ISE.",
                        "Generate the programming bitstream and download to the FPGA board.",
                        "Test all relevant input combinations using the toggle switches and observe the LED outputs."
                    ]
                }
            ]
        },
        "simulation": {
            "id": "simulation",
            "title": "Simulation / Execution",
            "isApplicable": true,
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "**Verilog Code for Full Adder Implementation:**"
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "language": "verilog",
                    "code": "module Fulladder(\n  input a,\n  input b,\n  input c,\n  output Sum,\n  output Carry\n);\n  assign Sum   = a ^ b ^ c;\n  assign Carry = (a & b) | (b & c) | (c & a);\nendmodule"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "**User Constraints File for Full Adder:**"
                },
                {
                    "type": "code",
                    "language": "properties",
                    "code": "NET \"a\"     LOC = \"P22\";\nNET \"b\"     LOC = \"P21\";\nNET \"c\"     LOC = \"P17\";\nNET \"Sum\"   LOC = \"P29\";\nNET \"Carry\" LOC = \"P27\";"
                },
                {
                    "type": "image",
                    "assetId": "exp04-fulladder-simulation-waveform",
                    "caption": "Simulation waveform for Full Adder: outputs Sum and Carry match the truth table for all 8 input combinations.",
                    "role": "simulation-screenshot"
                },
                {
                    "type": "text",
                    "content": "From the simulation waveform, the outputs Sum and Carry exactly match the expected outputs from the truth table. Initially all inputs are set to 0 and both outputs are low. Carry is high only when more than one input is high. When all inputs are 1, both outputs are also 1."
                }
            ]
        },
